<HEADLINE> South Africa Beats United States in Hopman Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- South Africa took a revenge of
the defending United States in a comeback 2-1 win in the Hopman
Cup tennis international mixed teams tournament Monday night in
Perth, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Wayne Ferreira and Amanda Coetzer reversed the results of last
year's final to steal the honor from the American pair of Jonathan
Stark and Chanda Rubin.
</P>
<P>
World No. 30th Rubin proved her domination of the South African
rival when she upset Coetzer 6-4, 6-3, as she did a year ago.
</P>
<P>
And the United States were clearly on the way of a nice start
for their bid for reigning the title when Stark led with a 6-3
first-game win in the following men's single.
</P>
<P>
But the third seeded South Africa steered up an astonishing
comeback and turn around the table.
</P>
<P>
Ferreira, ranked 43rd in the world and 52 places higher than
his opponent, won the next two game, 6-3, 6-4, and teamed up
Coetzer to stun the American dual 6-2, 5-7, 6-1 in the deciding
mixed doubles.
</P>
<P>
A total of eight teams will compete in two groups with a
round-robin format in the warm-up event for the Open.
</P>
<P>
Spain defeated Slovakia 2-1 in Monday's earlier match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
