<HEADLINE> Election of NPC Deputies for Taiwan Province to Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Election of 13 deputies from
Taiwan Province to the Ninth National People's Congress of China
is scheduled for January 8.
</P>
<P>
A group of 120 people of Taiwan origin from all over China are
holding a four-day meeting in the Taiwan Hall of the Great Hall of
the People in Beijing to draft a list of candidates for the final
ballot.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Kehui, a leading member of the meeting's presidium, said
today that the deputies will be elected for a term of five years.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth National People's Congress of China will be held in
the Chinese capital next March.  
</P>
