<HEADLINE> 1.8 Million Lusaka Teenage Girls Fall Pregnant in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1.8 million teenage
girls fell pregnant and aborted in Lusaka alone in the past three
years, the Zambia Association on Teenage Pregnancies and
Awareness has said.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia News Agency today quoted Chairperson of the
association Tamba Chinyembe as saying at the weekend that the
girls are mostly in the age group of between 12 and 21 years and
most of them live in high density townships of the capital city
with a population of about 250,000.
</P>
<P>
Nearly all the girls have a poverty background which forces
their parents to marry off their daughters soon after puberty,
she said.
</P>
<P>
She said a survey by the association shows that most of the
girls are now aborting or having plenty of children they are
unable to look after.
</P>
<P>
Most of the girls have been going to the Matero Referral
Clinic for specialist treatment especially when they attempt
abortions, she said.
</P>
<P>
The association plans to start an education campaign in these
townships to teach teenagers on the dangers of unplanned
pregancies and abortions.
</P>
<P>
Chinyembe said the organization will call for in its campaign
reproductive health methods such as contraceptives to protect
health of the girls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
