<HEADLINE> EU Grants Emergency Aid to Niger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
European Union (EU)'s executive body, has decided to grant an
emergency aid worth 7.15 million ECUs (about 8.5 million U.S.
dollars) to Niger, it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
The food aid of 3.75 million ECUs (approximately 4.5 million
dollars) will be mainly used to purchase 15,000 tonnes of cereals
for the most disadvantaged population groups in the country, the
Commission said in a press release issued here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The other part of the aid package will be used for aid
management and the activities of the Food-Producing Office of
Niger, a local organization in charge of food aid management.
</P>
<P>
The EU has been making efforts to solve the chronic food crisis
in Niger, the Commission said, adding that it made the decision
because the national security stock of Niger has been used up.
</P>
</TEXT>
