<DOCNO> XIE19980106.0026 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-05 18:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab Interior Ministers Condemn Violence, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Arab Interior Ministers
Council today strongly condemned all forms of violence and
terrorism whatever their sources.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released here at the end of the council's 15th
session, which began Sunday, the council said that such terrorist
activities constitute a grave threat to security, stability and
human rights.
</P>
<P>
It also expressed deep anxiety about the mounting acts of
violence and terrorism, emphasizing that such acts ought to be
confronted with appropriate and coordinated measures among all
countries.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed the need to enhance effective inter-Arab
security action in order to maintain the security and stability of
the Arab nation as well as the territorial integrity of Arab
states.
</P>
<P>
It speld out the necessity of distinguishing between terrorism
and the right of world peoples to fight by all means for the
liberation of their lands, in accordance with U.N. principles and
international laws.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the statement called upon those countries, in
which terrorist elements or groups reside, to deny them the right
to take refuge, to obtain funds or arms, or to practice any
criminal or propaganda activities that threaten the security and
safety of the Arab states.
</P>
<P>
It also urged those countries to promote security and judicial
cooperation with the Arab states, including the handing of
criminals, thus, enhancing effective confrontation and eradication
of terrorist activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
