<HEADLINE> Railroad Accident Kills 15 People in Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people were killed and 26
others injured in a railroad accident in north Tajikistan, the
Tajik government committee for emergency situations was quoted by
the Interfax as reporting on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report from Dushanbe said the accident occurred early
Monday near Karachkum when a passenger train from Andizhan to
Urgench collided with a freight train.
</P>
<P>
Only four of the dead have been identified, while eight of the
wounded were in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Tajik railroad administration said the
collision occurred after a pointsman mixed up track in a thick
fog, sending the passenger train from the first track to the sixth
in the direction of the freight train.
</P>
<P>
The rescue operation may last until late at night, the report
said. 
</P>
