<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Egypt to Sign Free Trade Zone Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Egypt will sign a
free trade zone agreement in March aimed at expanding trade and
economic cooperation between the two countries, Egyptian Minister
of Trade and Supply Ahmed Gowaili said here today.
</P>
<P>
Gowaili, who stopped over in Kuwait for a short visit on his
way to India, said a thorough study by a joint technical committee
on the agreement is almost over now.
</P>
<P>
He discussed with his Kuwaiti counterpart Jassem Al-Mudhaf the
latest developments of the study and a number of trade issues of
common concern.
</P>
<P>
He said the agreement will substantiate the 1991 Damascus
Declaration on inter-Arab coordination and cooperation, as well as
promote the economic cooperation among its signatories, namely,
the six Gulf Cooperation Council states, Egypt and Syria.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between Kuwait and Egypt currently stands at
100 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
