<HEADLINE> US Firms to Bid for Producing Choppers for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Two U.S. companies have
announced that they will compete for Turkey's defense tender of
producing 145 combat helicopters, the Anatolia News Agency quoted
a senior official as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Defense Industry Undersecretary Yalcir Burcek said that
Bell Helicopter Textron, the AH-1 Cobra producer, and the
renowned Boeing-McDonnell Douglas would participate in the
competition.
</P>
<P>
He said that companies from seven countries would like to gain
this defense contract worth 3 billion U.S. dollars, saying that
Turkey will evaluate their specific conditions before making a
decision.
</P>
<P>
Turkey, which has the second largest army in the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO) countries, has to import most of its
weapons, especially advanced systems, from the United States and
other Western countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
