<HEADLINE> Toshiba Leads in Whitbread Yacht Racing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- American yacht Toshiba took a
narrow lead in the fourth leg of the Whitbread round-the-world
yacht race on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba, skippered by Dennis Conner, was 1.5 nautical miles
ahead of Swedish Match at 1200 GMT. Third-placed Merit Cup was
14.1 miles behind the lead, followed by American entry Chessie
Racing with 32.8 miles back.
</P>
<P>
The nine-yacht fleet is expected to complete the 1270-mile
fourth leg from Sydney to Auckland by late Thursday night or early
Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
The seventh Whitbread race started in Southampton, England, on
September 21, last year and the first yachts are expected across
the finishing line in Southampton in late May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
