<HEADLINE> Customs Launches Crack Down on Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Customs authorities in China's
coastal areas have joined in the new round of the nationwide
crackdown on the smuggling of audio and visual products from
abroad.
</P>
<P>
According to information released during today's conference of
leading customs officers from coastal cities, local customs
offices in coastal areas will further give scope to their role in
cracking down on smuggling activities during 1998.
</P>
<P>
Conferees have been asked to summarize their experience from
previous campaigns in order to reinforce the crackdown and curb
the smuggling activities.
</P>
<P>
Available figures for the first 11 months of 1997 show that
coastal customs authorities confiscated a total of 9.12 million
smuggled tapes, discs and publications.  
</P>
</TEXT>
