<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 19.59 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 6 (Xinhua)-- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday lost 19.59 points to
3,719.62 as against Monday's close of 3,739.21.
</P>
<P>
The national index downed by 8.18 points to 1,619.21 from the
previous close of 1,627.39.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and US dollar index were quoted lower at 362.65 and
152.35 from the last close of 364.94 and 154.29 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Select pivotals suffered a setback on the market on selling
pressure from investors and domestic financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Brokers were nervous by the absence of foreign funds, which
remained on the sidelines following a sharp fall in the rupee
value against the US dollar. The downtrend in South Asian stock
markets also restricted the activity of the foreign institutional
investors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
