<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Light Industry Improves Product Mix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Projections for 1997 indicate
that the output value for China's light industry sector will hit
3,190 billion yuan (384 billion US dollars), with exports for the
year ending at 53 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Yu Zhen, chairman of the China National Council of Light
Industry, said today that the structure of the sector's product
mix improved noticeably during 1997, with more brand names gaining
national prominence.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-eight of 42 famous brand names established by the
National Industry and Commerce Administration are produced by the
light industry sector.
</P>
<P>
However, China's market for light industrial goods is far from
saturated, according to Yu. He said that China only produces some
260,000 of the 1.5 million-strong consumer goods available
worldwide, with 20-30 percent of the former goods developed over
the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo sent a congratulatory letter marking
the opening of the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980106.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Applies for More Than 10,000 Patents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 6 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province led the country in patent application in 1997 for the
third year, with more than 10,000 patents applied.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Guangdong Provincial Patent Bureau show
that by the end of last November, the province had approved
6,448 patents from 11,220 applicants, up 32.7 percent and 27.1
percent respectively over the corresponding period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province had made remarkable achievements in
transforming the patented technology into productive force, and
established some industries with their own intellectual property
rights.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey, the province last year increased its
output value by 9.1 billion yuan, its profits by some one billion
yuan, and foreign currency earnings by 90.2 million US
dollars, due to the spread of 51 pieces of patented technology.
</P>
<P>
The province had also issued laws and regulations,
including the Guangdong Province Patent Protection Ordinance, to
regulate the patent market and safeguard the inventors' and
consumers' rights and interests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
