<DOCNO> XIE19980106.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Melbourne Opens Office in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Australian city of Melbourne
opened an office today in Tianjin, one of China's four
municipalities and the largest coastal city in north China.
</P>
<P>
This office, the first of its kind opened by an Australian
local government, is jointly sponsored by the City of Melbourne,
the Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology (RMIT), the Taylors
Group and the Australia China Business Council of Victoria State.
</P>
<P>
The mayors of both cities attended today's opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Melbourne Mayor Ivan Deveson said that the office will promote
two-way trade and investment with Tianjin, China's third largest
city, as well as bilateral exchanges in the realm of education,
culture, and urban management.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin and Melbourne have enjoyed frequent business contacts
since the establishment of a sister-city relationship in 1980.
</P>
<P>
The RMIT has maintained long-term relations with the Chinese
government, as well as with industrial and educational departments
throughout China.
</P>
<P>
The Taylors Group signed an education and cooperation
agreement with the Tianjin No.1 Middle School in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Deveson said the office will serve as a bridge between
businesspeople from Melbourne, Victoria State and the Australian
government and business community, and will enable them to
conduct mutually beneficial trade cooperation with Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The Australia-China Business Council of Victoria State will
manage daily operations, according to Victoria State Council
President Bill O'Shea.
</P>
<P>
"Strengthening long-term business relations developed between
the cities over the years and the sister city relationship will
offer a positive environment for companies using the office,"
according to O'Shea.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that Tianjin has been and will continue to be a
magnet for foreign investment in China," said O'Shea, adding that
Tianjin is home to one of the best deepwater ports in the country.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is home to over 10,000 foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
