<DOCNO> XIE19980106.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Tightens Up Foreign Exchange Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet Tuesday
approved a few measures aimed at preventing Thai exporters and
individuals from holding foreign currencies for a long time,
according to a Government House press release.
</P>
<P>
In order to bolster the supply of foreign currencies, the
cabinet requires that exporters bring in foreign currencies
immediately after the payment is received.
</P>
<P>
Under the previous rules, exporters have 120 days following the
shipment of their goods to bring in their foreign currencies.
</P>
<P>
The 120-day deadline leaves loopholes for some exporters who
receive payment in less than 120 days.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet also requires that Thai exporters and residents who
receive foreign currencies for their goods and services should
convert or deposit the sums in banks within seven days, instead of
the previous 15 days, so as to speed up foreign currency
liquidity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
