<HEADLINE> Courier Out of Australian Hardcourt Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Former world top tennis player
American Jim Courier was eliminated by Australian doubles
specialist Mark Woodforde on Tuesday's first-round match at the
Austalian men's hardcourt championship in Adelaide, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Courier, world number 21st, lost to Woodforde 7-5,
6-2 in the warm-up tournament for the Australia Open.
</P>
<P>
