bound of exiting when rain fell.
</P>
<P>
Armenia's Sargis Sargisian stepped out of Adelaide's Memorial
Drive with a 6-4 first-game win and leading 3-2 in the second,
after organisers postponed the match to Wednesday for the
interrupted rain.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten also benefited from weather as his
tie against Sweden's Kenneth Carlsen was abandoned on Tuesday.
The French Open champion arrived at courtside about an hour before
his scheduled match after his flight from Rio de Janeiro, Brazil,
had been delayed.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's other key matches, fourth seeded Magnus Norman of
Sweden beat Christian Ruud of Norway 6-3, 1-6, 6-4, while
Woodforde's doubles partner Todd Woodbridge beat Martin Damm of
the Czech Republic 7-5, 4-6, 6-3. 
