<HEADLINE> URGENT: Indonesia Unveils Budget for 1998/99 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia, the world's fourth
most populous country which is struggling to overcome a monetary
crisis, Tuesday announced a balanced budget for the 1998/99 fiscal
year (April 1-March 31).
</P>
<P>
In a nationally televised address to the House of People's
Representatives Tuesday evening, President Soeharto submitted a
133.49 trillion rupiah (about 33.37 billion U.S. dollars at the
current exchange rate of 4,000 per dollar) draft budget, a
32.1-percent increase over the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The 1997/98 budget, unveiled in January last year, set the
government's spending and income to balance at 101 trillion rupiah
(42.8 billion dollars at the exchange rate of that time).
</P>
</TEXT>
