<HEADLINE> Date, Venue Set for Mass Burial of Air Crash Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A mass burial for the 104
passengers and crew members who were killed in last month's crash
of SilkAir Flight MI185 in Palembang, Indonesia, will be held in
the Botanical Park of Palembang on January 19, Singapore
television said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The television report said this was announced by Singapore
Communications Minister Mah Bow Tan and Indonesian Transport
Minister Haryanto Dhanutirto at a joint news conference in
Palembang on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The site for the mass burial, the Botanical Park, is said to be
some two kilometers from the town's airport and the date is
exactly one month after the crash. SilkAir Flight MI185 went down
on December 19, 1997, on its way back to Singapore from Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
Singapore television said the burial site was chosen because of
its accessibility and because it can be prepared faster.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a monument will be built near the crash site for
the victims, it said. Flight MI185 crashed into the Musi River
near Palembang.
</P>
<P>
The two black boxes of the ill-fated plane, the flight data
recorder and the cockpit voice recorder, had both been recovered
in the search and rescue operation which started shortly after the
mishap took place.
</P>
<P>
But no survivors were ever found, not even a single complete
body. So far about 50 percent of the plane's wreckage has been
recovered and dredging operations on the Musi River will continue
until next Wednesday as there is a need for investigators to
recover critical wreckage, the television report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
