<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Takes Steps to Control VC Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China, a major vitamin C (VC)
exporter, has decided to take steps to tighten macro-control on VC
production and export so as to ensure this industry would go out
of its all-time low and develop in a healthy way.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Relations, China will, starting from this year, limit VC
production scope to ensure a reasonable pricing for VC exports.
</P>
<P>
China will not build new VC plants and expand the production
capacity of the existing ones, said Liu Junsheng, an official
in the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The State Pharmaceutical Administration will issue production
permit certificates for VC plants. Without the certificates, VC
plants will not be entitled to export VC, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will re-examine the business qualification
of VC export companies, and put the VC export price under strict
control. Those firms, which have lowered their export price without
official approval, will be punished.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be made to expand the domestic market so as to
digest the already enlarged VC production capacity.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that the measures are taken against the
international background that the VC supply is much bigger than
the demand and China's VC firms have suffered heavy losses due to
fierce competition on the international and domestic markets.
</P>
<P>
Liu said, the international VC price has dropped to
the current five US dollars per kilogram from 12 dollars two year
ago.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China exports some 20,000 tons of VC each
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
