<HEADLINE> Nagano Torch Relay under Way in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Symbolic torches for the 1998
Nagano Winter Olympic Games started their relay progress through
Japan on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The torch relay set off from three Japanese cities of Sapporo,
Okinawa and Kagoshima.
</P>
<P>
Carrying the torch in Sapporo, scene of the 1972 winter
Olympics, was 53-year-old Akitsugu Konno, who took a silver medal
in ski jumping in 1972 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
All three routes end up in Nagano on the eve of the February
7 opening ceremony. The torch was ignited in Athens, site of the
ancient Olympics, and flown to Tokyo where it was split for the
three relays.
</P>
<P>
Some 7,000 runners will be involved in the month-long relay.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nagano organisers breathed a sigh of relief at
the region's first substantial snowfall this season, which
delivered about 15 centimeters. 
</P>
