<HEADLINE> Household Electronics Appliances Holds Big Market Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Once a loser in competing for
domestic buyers' loyalty, the Chinese brands of household
electronics appliances now boasts a far bigger market share than
their foreign rivals, said a survey report publicized by the State
Statistical Bureau and the China Statistical Society today.
</P>
<P>
The results of the survey, which was based on the figures from
600 department stores in 121 cities, showed the market share of
domestic brands exceeded 70 percent for eight out of ten major
household electronics products.
</P>
<P>
The market share of domestic brands of freezer, electric rice
pot, refrigerator, VCD player and household washing machine stood
at 99.21 percent, 95.92 percent, 94.49 percent, 86.86 percent and
82.58 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
That of color television, household air-conditioner and
microwave oven was 81.36 percent, 74.22 percent and 70.99 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, the market share for Chinese acoustic equipment and
video recorders is lower than the foreign brands, standing at
47.05 percent and 3.4 percent, respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
