<HEADLINE> Shanghai Residents Support Hope Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The well-off residents in
Shanghai have found that they have a stronger attachment to the
Hope Project, which began in the metropolis three years ago.
</P>
<P>
To date, the residents of Shanghai, China's industrial city, have
donated over 66 million yuan to the Hope Project, funding the
establishment of 380 Hope Project schools and helping 33,000
dropouts to return to schools.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Province, in southwest China, received 4.8 million
yuan of donation from Shanghai in 1997, which has been used in
buildinging 110 Hope Project schools and bringing back some 1,000
dropouts to schools.
</P>
<P>
Unlike three years ago, when people offer donations on impulse,
an increasing number of Shanghai residents have donated regularly
on the ground that they regard it an obligation to help those who
are in need of help.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of 1998, the city has organized four
outdoor activities in Shanghai, encouraging more public
involvement in the Hope Project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
