<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Italy's double Olympic champion
Deborah Compagnoni won a women's World Cup Alpine skiing giant
slalom in Bormioi, Italy on Tuesday to take her unbeaten run in
the discipline to nine races.
</P>
<P>
The local skier, now unbeaten in giant slalom for more than a
year with eight successive World Cup wins and the 1997 world
championship victory, left her rivals trailing with a time of two
minutes 20.38 seconds.
</P>
