<HEADLINE> China to Open First Environment Protection Products Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China's first multi-functional
market exclusively for environmental protection products will open
soon in the country's leading industrial center of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Apart from engaging mainly in the trade of environmental
protection products, the market is also expected to provide
service for the development of products for environmental
protection and construction of environmental protection projects.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the market will also provide information of the
industry and arrange related personnel exchange.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 100 research institutions or ventures for
making environment protection products have registered with the
market, which is to occupy a floor space of 3,000 square meters,
to open boothes there.
</P>
<P>
The market is sponsored jointly by the Shanghai Environmental
Protection Bureau, Hongkou District Government and Shanghai
Environment Science Research Institute, which are expected to
collect 80 million yuan (9.6 million US dollars) to build a new
building for the market.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Wang Naidun, director of the Hongkou District
Environmental Protection Bureau, said, the market plans to collect
the latest information of the environmental protection industry
both in China and from overseas with its computer networks, now
under way, and to turn itself into a national information center
of the environmental protection industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
