<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline on the Singapore market on Tuesday as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) lost 56.83 points to close
at 1,439.12 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said stock prices plunged by 3.8 percent as the
regional currencies took another beating and market sentiment was
dealt a blow by tumbling regional currencies.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. dollar continued its stride against all major
currencies in Asian trading where the Southeast Asian currencies
declined. The Singapore dollar lost 280 points against the U.S.
dollar to close at 1.7365.
</P>
<P>
The dealers said that while losses were across-the-board, the
property shares took the most severe beating. But some light
bargain hunting lifted the STII off its low of 1,423.25 during the
day's trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 125.42 million units, worth
268.93 million Singapore dollars (about 154.56 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to overwhelm advances by 346 to 32,
while 233 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Technologies Engineering was the most actively
traded counter as it registered a turnover of 8.24 million units.
It was followed by DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Land which
had 3.58 million shares traded. RHB Capital was next with 2.99
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Airlines (SIA) Foreign led the gainers of the day
as it rose by 30 cents to finish at 10.9 Singapore dollars.
Jardine Matheson Holdings (JMH) 500 increased by 23 cents to end
at 2.8 U.S. dollars, while JMH 400 picked up by 20 cents to close
at 5.5 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 2.4 dollars to end at 33.6 Singapore dollars. Bukit
Sembawang fell by 90 cents to close at 10.1 Singapore dollars.
Roth Malaya lost 70 cents to finish at 12.3 Singapore dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
