<HEADLINE> Macao Police Step Up Protection of Gold Shops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Macao police sent out more patrol
vehicles on Tuesday in a bid to better protect gold shops from
armed robbery.
</P>
<P>
At the request of local gold shop owners, more police cars and
policemen appeared in the downtown area where gold shops are
located.
</P>
<P>
A group of gold shop owners visited the headquarters of local
security police on Monday, saying they were deeply worried about
the recent wave of robberies of gold shops. They requested more
police presence near their shops.
</P>
<P>
A senior officer of the Security Police Department agreed to
their request while asking them to increase contacts with police
and improve their anti-theft monitoring systems.
</P>
<P>
The officer said some of the video tapes taken from the
monitoring systems of robbed shops show only the back of the
robbers and they are thus useless for police investigation.
</P>
<P>
The owners promised improvements. They say police presence is
more effective than other means such as hiring guards or buying
more insurance.
</P>
<P>
A number of armed robbery cases occurred recently, even in the
 downtown area at daytime. Losses are estimated at more than one
million patacas (about 125,000 U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
