<HEADLINE> Pierce Leads France to Bruise Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Mary Pierce and Cedric Pioline
beat their singles opponent each to notch an early victory when
France bruised Germany 3-0 on Tuesday at the Hopman Cup team
tennis tournament in Perth, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Pierce, runner-up of last year's Australian Open to Martina
Hingis, displayed a class-above match against Germany's Anke
Huber, winning 4-6, 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Pioline clinched the victory when he beat Tommy Haas 6-4, 6-4
in the second singles.
</P>
<P>
France sealed the win by edged the German pair 2-6, 6-3, 7-3 in
the final mixed doubles in the round-robin tie.
</P>
<P>
France will meet the United States, which were beaten by South
Africa on Monday, in Thursday's match.
</P>
<P>
Eight teams in two round-robin groups of four teams each are
competing in the 10th Hopman Cup, a warm-up event for the coming
Open.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Enqvist teams up with Asa Carlsson for Sweden to square
with the Slovak Republic wildcard entrants Karol Kucera and Karina
Habsudova later on Tuesday. 
