<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Great Los Angeles Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, January 5 (Xinhua) -- A minor earthquake shocked
the Great los Angeles area at 10:14 Monday morning and there has
been no immediate reports of any death or damage.
</P>
<P>
The quake was of 4.3 magnitude on the Richter scale and the
epicenter was in southwest of Chino, a San Bernardino County
community 46 miles east of downtown Los Angeles, according to
Robert Tindol, a spokesman for the California Institute of
Technology in north Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
There has been no reports of any death or damage in Los Angeles
County, said Fire Department Inspector Henry Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
Great Los Angeles area is on the south end of the long seismic
belt stretching up to San Francisco in the north of California,
which experienced quakes and tremors much more often than other
parts of the country. 
</P>
