<HEADLINE> China Calls for Vigilance Against Activities to Split China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- China hopes that some countries
would guard against the activities by the Taiwan authorities,
making use of the current financial turmoil in southeast Asia, to
create "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan", or to undermine
the relations between these countries and China.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Shen Guofang in response to a question concerning the recent visit
of Taiwan's "vice-president" Lien Chan to Singapore on "vacation"
at a press conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that Singapore, as a member of the United Nations
and a country having formal diplomatic ties with China, would
observe the related UN resolutions on the Taiwan issue and abide
by the principles set in the Sino-Singaporean joint communique on
the establishment of diplomatic relations, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
China does not oppose unofficial contacts between countries and
Taiwan but it opposes the practice of any country having
diplomatic ties with China to forge any form of official relations
or contacts with Taiwan, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
