<HEADLINE> 15 Killed, 60 Injured in Train Accident in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people were killed
and more than 60 others injured when a passenger train rammed into
a stationary express train in Uttar Pradesh's Moradabad division
late Monday night due to thick fog, railway officials said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary investigations revealed that the driver of the
passenger train had overshot the signal due to poor visibility
caused by dense fog, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Railway Minister Ram Vilas Paswan has ordered an inquiry into
the accident.
</P>
<P>
Railway board officials have rushed to the scene to supervise
relief and rescue operations, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Train services in the section have been affected and all mail
and express trains were diverted.  
</P>
