<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese City Opening Wider </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province, has come up with a plan to improve the
use of overseas investment and to increase cooperation with other
countries to help its economy.
</P>
<P>
Most of overseas funds will be used to improve tourism, finance
and investment sectors. It will introduce 10 cooperative projects
involving 30 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the city has approved 3,600 overseas-funded
projects, attracting 6 billion US dollars of overseas investment,
with technology and urban infrastructure accounting for a large
number.
</P>
<P>
The city now has 14 overseas-funded projects that involve 30
million US dollars of investment each and it is expected to have
at least 1.3 billion US dollars of foreign trade for 1997, an
increase of 41 percent since 1992.
</P>
<P>
As a state-level development project, the Shenyang Economic and
Technological Development Zone has introduced 470 million US
dollars of overseas investment to set up 620 enterprises, which
can earn 400 million US dollars in foreign trade a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
