<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT January 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN - An Iranian airliner with 113 people on board made an
emergency landing in a desert in central Iran Monday night due to
technical failure, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The airliner with 104 passengers and 9 crew members was on a
domestic flight from Orumiye, West Azarbaijan province to Iran's
capital city of Tehran. But due to the bad weather, the passenger
plane could not land on Tehran airport and was directed to Iran's
central city of Isfahan. (Iran-Airliner-Emergency Landing)
</P>
