</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- Forty-five people have died in the cold spell that
has swept Bangladesh in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
Eight deaths were reported on Monday in the districts of
Sirajganj and Kushtia, respectively northwest and west of this
capital city, press reports said here
Tuesday. (Bangladesh-Cold-Deaths)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thai Finance Minister Tarrin Nimmanhaeminda has
moved ahead his planned meeting with International Monetary Fund
(IMF) officials to review the terms on the IMF providing a 17.2
billion U.S. dollar bailout package.
</P>
<P>
