<HEADLINE> Providing Technical Training for Farmers in Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A large number of farmers in
China's Anhui Province have gotten training in agricultural
techniques in the past few years, thanks to the local government.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, local government has placed priority on providing
farmers with more basic farming, animal-husbandry, and
fruit-planting skills.
</P>
<P>
By now, 3.55 million local farmers have received the training,
and a small army of 70,000 rural technicians has been set up, in
addition to 30,000 technological demonstration households and more
than 200,000 members of technology associations.
</P>
<P>
The province also has 1,182 science and technology associations
for farmers, at the town or township level, and 2,710 special
agricultural skills research societies. 
</P>
