<HEADLINE> Zambia to Liberalize Oil Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will this year liberalize
oil imports to help lower petroleum product prices, the Financial
Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to the weekly newspaper, the country's energy
regulatory board has decided to liberalize the import of crude
oil feedstocks this year.
</P>
<P>
From now on anybody who has all the necessary requirements and
permits will be allowed to import oil feedstock, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Zambia's fuel prices are the highest in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia National Oil Company spent about 80 million U.S.
dollars on crude oil imports last year, the newspaper said,
adding that it is likely to spend less this year thanks to the
liberalization policy. 
