<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Taiwan Exchanges Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Exchanges between Shanghai and
Taiwan spread into other fields with newer programs last year.
</P>
<P>
They had 363 bilateral exchange programs last year, with
educational and cultural programs accounting for the majority,
according to the Taiwan Affairs Office of the Shanghai Municipal
Government.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to exchanges between institutions of higher learning,
academic seminars and lectures became more common.
</P>
<P>
Huai Opera, which is popular in northern Jiangsu Province but
which received scant attention previously, aroused the interest of
Taiwan residents when it was performed on the island.
</P>
<P>
Other cultural exchanges like the Kun Opera, puppet shows, and
exhibitions were successful on the island. And some Taiwan
organizations for the arts sent groups to Shanghai, and a music
festival was held there.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between television stations increased last year as
well, and there was a special program during the Moon Festival
with a live broadcast for television viewers on both sides of the
Taiwan Straits via satellite.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges of telecommunications personnel also took on a new
look, and some unofficial scientific and commercial organizations
established channels for future exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
