million U.S. dollars of pledged investment in 1997, the Times of
Zambia reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted latest statistics from the country's
Investment Centre as saying that about 140 investment licences
were issued in agricultural, manufacturing, tourism, transport,
service, construction, fisheries and mining sectors.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that a total of 6200 jobs will be created by
these investments.
</P>
<P>
The largest amount of investment was in the manufacturing
industry which recorded 85.5 million dollars in pledged
investment with about 1400 jobs to be created, according to the
paper.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is the largest investor which pledged about 31
million dollars in the manufacturing sector while China ranked
the second with about 19.7 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia Association of Manufacturers Chairman Mark
O'Dennell attributed the growth in investment to the liberalised
economy and the 1997 budget which encouraged investment in the
industry. 
