<HEADLINE> Shanghai Does Nearly Three Trillion Yuan In Securities Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Securities trading on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange was worth nearly three trillion yuan in 1997,
according to recent figures.
</P>
<P>
Ninety companies were listed to the bourse and 93 types of new
stocks were floated, 85 of them in A-shares, for local investors,
and the others in B-shares, for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
The former raised 37.6 billion yuan, and the latter, 786
million US dollars, increases of 115.88 percent and 237.34 percent
respectively, from 1996.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of trade was 2.98 trillion yuan, with 12.28
billion yuan in daily trading, up 9.66 percent from 1996. The SSE
Index moved up steadily, fluctuating in a range between 900 and
1,500 points.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, there were 383 firms listed, with a
total of 106.24 billion shares and a total capitalization of 921.8
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has 17.13 million registered investors. The SSE had
467 member companies with a total of 5,703 seats at the bourse, 91
percent of them from other parts of the country and accounting for
78 percent of the trading.
</P>
<P>
The SSE has become the country's largest stock and bond
market. 
</P>
