<HEADLINE> Beijing's Largest Shopping Plaza to Reopen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The New Dong'an Mansion,
Beijing's largest commercial center, will open again on January 18
after four years of construction
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Daily reports that the 220,000-sq m plaza, which
has a shopping centers, offices, restaurants, and entertainment
centers, cost 386 million US dollars to build.
</P>
<P>
It is located on Wangfujing Street, a busy shopping
center in downtown Beijing. The store is computerized for quicker
sales and inventory.
</P>
<P>
Dong'an has a history of more than 100 years, and is a familiar
name for the citizens of Beijing. An antiques street on the
market's ground floor, recaptures the flavor of the old Dong'an
market with teahouses and antique shops.
</P>
<P>
The New Dong'an Market is managed by Hong Kong's Sun Hung Kai
Properties Ltd. and the Dong'an Group. It has dozens of specialty
shops selling famous name-brand products like Nike, Crocodile, and
Pierre Cardin.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Daily says that there will be warehouses and cinemas
open in the Dong'an Mansion later this year. 
</P>
