<HEADLINE> China Approves Major Chemical Fertilizer Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Jiujiang Chemical
Fertilizer Project received state approval recently, making it the
country's first large fertilizer manufacturer to be completed
during the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
Its location is the city of Jiujiang in Jiangxi Province With
its annual capacity of 300,000 tons of synthetic ammonia and
520,000 tons of urea, it is the largest and the most advanced
operation in the province, with equipment imported from Germany,
Italy, Japan and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Construction work began in December 1992 and trial operation
started in October 1996. It is part of the Jiujiang Chemical
General Plant, and was jointly funded by the province and the
China Petro-Chemical Corporation and built at a cost of nearly
three billion yuan. 
</P>
