<HEADLINE> Eritrea to Import Fishing Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Eritrean Minister of
Fisheries Petros Solomon has disclosed that his country plans to
import from 60 to 100 fishing boats to develop its fishing
industry.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest issue of the English weekly Eritrea
Profile, the minister said a study over the past few years has
confirmed that the country has a potential of catching between 50
to 100 thousand tons of various fishes annually.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the entire Eritrean population is not yet
familiarized with fish since activities of fisheries and the
culture of the fish is confined to the coast area.
</P>
<P>
As the amount of fish is deteriorating around the world, the
minister said Eritrea could take advantage of this in exploiting
the rich potential it has in fishing.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that his ministry is making preparations to sign
a contract with companies of good repute so that the country
would earn substantial foreign currency from the products of
these sector.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea has a coast line of 1,300 Kilometers and more than 360
islands. Researches indicate that the Eritrean water territory
shelters various species of fish, rich coral reef and pearl.
</P>
</TEXT>
