<HEADLINE> Legal Assistance in South China improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 6 (Xinhua) -- A legal assistance system that
emerged in Guangzhou, the capital of China's Guangdong Province,
about two years ago, is showing signs of maturity.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, which was in the vanguard in China's opening-up
drive, was a logical place for the Guangzhou Legal Assistance
Center, which opened in November 1995 as the country's first
center of its kind. A number of regulations on the use of legal
assistance have been developed by the city to help the development
of the center.
</P>
<P>
It has a large group of lawyers, some of them part-time, some
full-time.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, the center has dealt with 600 criminal and
civil cases, including one involving a 15-million-yuan robbery in
Guangdong's Fanyu, which put the center in the public eye.
</P>
<P>
A Guangzhou Youth Legal Assistance Office and the Guangzhou
Youth Legal Assistance Foundation were also recently established
in Guangzhou. 
</P>
