<HEADLINE> Cold Wave Claims 45 Lives in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Forty-five people have died in the
cold spell that has swept Bangladesh in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
Eight deaths were reported on Monday in the districts of
Sirajganj and Kushtia, respectively northwest and west of this
capital city, press reports said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In Jamalpur and Pabna districts, also northwest and west of
here respectively, nine people died because of the severe cold on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the cold wave has claimed 45 lives since it began
about a week ago.
</P>
<P>
The cold wave, which meteorological officials said might
intensify in the next two or three days, has paralyzed normal life
in many parts of the country, particularly in the north and west.
</P>
<P>
Winter normally is the most pleasant season in the country,
when the temperatures are between 13.5 and 26.5 degrees Celsius.
</P>
</TEXT>
