<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Airliner Makes Emergency Landing in Desert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 6 (Xinhua) - An Iranian airliner with 113
people on board made an emergency landing in a desert in central
Iran Monday night due to technical failure, Tehran radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
The airliner with 104 passengers and 9 crew members was on a
domestic flight from Orumiye, West Azarbaijan province to Iran's
capital city of Tehran. But due to the bad weather, the passenger
plane could not land on Tehran airport and was directed to Iran's
central city of Isfahan.
</P>
<P>
Around 2200 local times (1830 GMT) Monday night, the plane
disappeared on the control radar, Tehran radio quoted an official
from the country's aviation organization as saying. But it was
found later through radio communication with pilot of the plane
that the plane had made an emergency landing in the desert, east
of Isfahan.
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami has ordered the relief aid
groups to rush to the site to rescue the people on board the
plane.
</P>
<P>
So far no details about possible casualties and damages have
been reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
