<HEADLINE> 2 Explosions in Macedonia Target Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Two bombs exploded near police
offices in Macedonia on Sunday, causing some property losses,
Agiensia Telegrafike Shqiptare (ATA), the official Albanian news
agency, reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Macedonian police said that policemen were the targets of the
two blasts, which occurred at 21:35 (local time) in southern
Macedonia's Kumanovo and at 21:50 (local time) in middle
Macedonia's Prilep, respectively. The bomb that exploded in Prilep
was placed in a police car.
</P>
<P>
Five cars were wrecked, and the doors and windows of the police
offices and nearby houses were broken during the explosions.
</P>
<P>
The perpetrators of the bomb blasts were still unidentified,
according to the police. 
