<HEADLINE> Venezuela Earns Big Revenue From Privatization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan government earned
over 128 million U.S. dollars from privatization in 1997,
Investment Fund officials said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The public auction of Orinoco Steel, which was the largest and
most important company sold last year, made up the biggest share
of the sum.
</P>
<P>
The auction also included cement manufacturing companies and
three hotels, which belonged to the Venezuelan Corporation of
Tourism.
</P>
<P>
Capitals from the privatization will be directed to pay foreign
debts, in accordance with the recently amended Privatization Law.
</P>
<P>
A share of the capitals obtained from the auction of Venezuelan
Corporation of Guava Apple will be used to fund regional
development projects. 
