<HEADLINE> IAAF Will Not Erase Former East German's Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur
Athletic Federation IAAF refused the complaints from British to
erase world records or titles from former East German athletes on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
IAAF said it was impossible under its rules to deny
performances from the former East Germans in the 1970s and 1980s
though athletes admitted to taking performance-enhancing drugs.
</P>
<P>
"The rule is quite clear," said IAAF spokesman Georgio
Reineri. "After six years it is not possible to cancel any
results. It is too late. At this stage there are no plans (to
change the results)." 
