<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment in Indonesia to Reach 5.8 million in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment in Indonesia with
the economy growing at an estimated 3.5 percent is predicted to
increase by 1.4 million in 1998, while in 1997 the unemployment
people totaled 4.4 million, government sources said.
</P>
<P>
According to data released by the Ministry of Manpower on
Monday, if the economy is growing by only 3.5 percent in 1998, as
economists have predicted, only 1.3 million of the 2.7 million
increase in the workforce would be get a job this year.
</P>
<P>
Thus, unemployed people would increase by 1.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, workers associations and employers organizations
have estimated that 800,000 workers in the property and
construction sector lost their job, while 300,000 in the textile
and garment industries have been laid off, and another 100,000 in
some other sectors have been dismissed.
</P>
<P>
Analysts have warned that unemployment rate in the country
would rise from seven percent of the total 90 million-strong
workforce in 1995 to 11 percent in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Since the monetary crisis hit the country early July, a lot of
middle and small factories have been closed. The Indonesia rupiah
has lost more than 100 percent of its value against the U.S.
dollar in the past seven months.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Indonesia's economic growth was 7.8 percent. Some
economists predicted the growth will drop to 5 percent in 1997 and
2 to 3 percent in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Stagflation, in which economic growth reached only 3.5 percent,
while inflation may reach two digits, will lower the purchasing
power of the people, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
To overcome all these economic ills, the ministry held that
liquidity must be enhanced, public confidence in the government
must be restored, and transparency in monetary and economic
policies would be a necessity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980106.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
