<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Performance of Large State Firms Sound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The performance of China's 1,254
large state-owned firms was sound and they have backed the stable
growth of the nation's economy, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
"These firms are the new hope of the country's economic
development," said the Beijing-based English language newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output of these firms reached 958.8 billion yuan
in the first 11 months of last year, accounting for 40.9 percent
of the total output of the 67,000 state firms.
</P>
<P>
They earned 1,523 billion yuan from sales, 60 percent of the
total, said the paper, adding that their profits reached 72.1
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
There are 23 firms achieving annual sales of more than 10
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
"These firms are mainly to be found in such sectors as oil
exploration, electric power and transportation," said the paper.
</P>
<P>
The paper also noted that only 30.7 percent of the total large
ones suffered losses, the lowest level in recent years.
</P>
<P>
These firms have increased their assets as a result of the
accelerated pace of merger and reconstruction, said the paper,
noting that the net assets of the firms reached 1,414 billion yuan
by the end of November last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
