<DOCNO> XIE19980106.0253 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Bottoms at 6,700 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 6 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian currency of
rupiah hit a historic low of 6,700 against the U.S. dollar Monday
on continuing corporate demand for dollar and weakness in regional
currency markets, dealers here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Spot rupiah closed at 6,600/6,700 to the dollar against the
opening of 6,000/6,100 in the morning session.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah has lost more than 100 percent of its value against
the greenback since early July last year.
</P>
<P>
"People in Jakarta panicked after they saw the rupiah surpass
6,700 during the lunch break. But we could do nothing about it," a
dealer with a local private bank said.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the central bank was not seen in the spot market
Monday like it was in the previous trading days.
</P>
<P>
"The central bank's intervention in the spot market would not
even be effective now when the rupiah continues to free-fall," one
dealer said.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also said political concerns ahead of the convening of
the People's Consultative Assembly in March to elect a president
and vice president accelerated the fall of the rupiah against the
dollar.
</P>
<P>
As the rupiah weakened, stock prices on the Jakarta Stock
Exchange closed slightly higher after declining in the morning
trading session.
</P>
<P>
The composite index closed 0.18 points higher to 410.29 with
258.95 million shares changing hands in the regular market valued
at 40 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Securities analysts said they had not seen any reason for the
stock market to rise when the rupiah continued to weaken against
the dollar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
