<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile, Sweden Sign Cooperation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Chile and
Sweden signed today in Santiago a cooperation accord on economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Chilean President Eduardo Frei and visiting Swedish Prime
Minister Goran Persson headed the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The bilateral cooperation will include areas such as the
maintenance of forests and the timber industry, environment,
development and integration of middle and small-sized businesses
and training for workers.
</P>
<P>
Both countries will also cooperate on sharing technology for
public works, central, regional and local management, as well as
customs and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Chile and Sweden also inked a document for cooperation on
education, subscribed by Ministers of Education from both nations.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish Premier arrived in Chile Sunday and met Monday
President Frei, Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza and Public
Works Ministry Ricardo Lagos.
</P>
<P>
The officials spoke on bilateral economic and commercial ties,
interchange of technology for public infrastructure and the
possible Chile`S purchase of Swedish warplanes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
