<HEADLINE> Inflation In Argentina up 0.3 Percent in 1997, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The inflation rate in
Argentina rose by 0.3 percent over 1997, reported Monday the
National Institute of Statistics and Census.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, domestic prices at wholesales dropped 0.9 percent
last year, due to a low in prices of national products like raw
materials, manufactured goods and electric power.
</P>
<P>
The institute said that retail sales prices went up due mainly
to an increase in the entertainment industry and a 4.7 surge in
the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Last December, sectors of health, food and beverages registered
a 0.1-percent prices lift while housing and household appliances
prices kept unvariable. 
</P>
