<HEADLINE> Purchasing Power Of Argentine Workers Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Purchasing power of
manufacturing workers rose by 0.6 percent in November 1997,
against the same month 1996, reported Monday a study of the
Argentina University for Business.
</P>
<P>
The institution said that the increment of the workers` income
is due to the stability of prices and wages, as well as to the
expansion of credits for comsumption.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the university underlined the low inflation rate as
a favorable factor for a rising workers` purchasing power.
</P>
<P>
From November 96 to November 97, salaries rose in sectors like
automobile, cement, metallurgy and petrochemistry, the document
said. 
