<HEADLINE> Gingrich Plans to Seek Tax Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Speaker Newt Gingrich of the
House of Representatives said Monday he has a plan for a "smarter,
more modern government" that includes a combined maximum 25
percent tax bite from all three levels of government.
</P>
<P>
In a speech before the Cobb County Chamber of Commerce in his
hometown of Marietta, Georgia., Gingrich said his "Goals for a
Generation" should serve as the Republican agenda for the 21st
century, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich called for a National Commission on Retirement to
review Social Security, and also urged improvements in public
schools plagued by high dropout rates and said all students should
learn to read English by the fourth grade.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich said he supported gradual tax cuts so that peacetime
taxation by federal, state and local government does not take more
than 25 percent of a person's income.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Tax collection of some kind is going to be with us.
The current abusive system with the current quotas for collections
and the current infringements on personal liberty clearly can be
replaced."
</P>
<P>
Gingrich said Social Security reform would not require "painful
choices."
</P>
<P>
He said, "The power of compound interest means that young
people today ought to have a better return on their investment and
a higher value added and ought to be able to retire with more
money, not less." 
</P>
</TEXT>
