<HEADLINE> EU Voices Concern Over Violence in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
voiced its deep concern on the reported killing of hundreds of
people over the past few days, calling for an immediate end to the
violence.
</P>
<P>
Some 500 civilians have been reportedly killed in the first six
days of the holy Moslem month of Ramadan and the Armed Islamic
Group was likely to be blamed for most of those massacres.
</P>
