<HEADLINE> One Killed, 60 Injured in U.S. Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- One was killed and at least
60 others were injured when a bus ran off a highway and rolled
over in New Mexico early today, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The bus was traveling from El Paso, Texas, to Denver, Colorado,
when it crashed at about 1:30 a.m. (0830 GMT) on Interstate 25 in
an area southeast of Santa Fe, New Mexico's capital city. It
struck a guard rail before landing on its side on the shoulder.
</P>
<P>
State police investigators did not immediately know what caused
the crash. But the road condition appeared good.
</P>
<P>
A 31-year-old man was killed and at least 60 people, including
the driver, were taken to hospitals in Albuquerque, Las Vegas and
Santa Fe. Hospital officials said some were in critical or
serious condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
